      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''Publishers Use Secrecy in Harry Potter Promotion'' (Business Day, May 22):</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''Publishers Use Secrecy in Harry Potter Promotion'' (Business Day, May 22):</p>
        <p>As a devoted buyer of Harry Potter books for my 12-year-old sister, I am sure that children will be anticipating the release of this latest book. Children will look forward to seeing the fancy cover and wonder what the plot is this time.</p>
        <p>But I wonder how many children are going to get through 600 pages. Compared with the normal 300 pages, this is a drastic change. Indeed, the plot may remain a mystery even after the book is released, because children will have a hard time finishing the book.</p>
        <p>ARRIA WRIGHT  Boston, May 22, 2000</p>
      </block>
